

# ==== Format ====
# prefix(scope): :emoji: Commit body...
#
# backlog task key

# ==== prefix ====
# fix: FIX bug and typo
# feat: Add new features
# refactor: Refactoring
# style: Changes related to style like css/sass
# chore: Maintenance for file move, delete, rename and so on
# test: Fix or changes for test features
# docs: Changes documents
# breaking: Disructive changes
# build: Changes build processing(maven, gradle, gulp, webpack, etc.)
# ci: Configurations CI/CD
# pref: Improvements performance
# revert: Revert changes
# other: others

# ==== Emojis ====
# ----- project / features -----
# 🎉 :tada:                 Begin a project!
# ✨ :sparkles:             Introduce new features
# 💥 :boom:                 Introduce breaking changes
# 👍 :+1:                   Additional partial features
# ----- refactor -----
# ♻️️ :recycle:              Refactor code
# 💬 :speech_balloon:       Add or update text and literals
# 💡 :bulb:                 Add or update comments in source code
# 🔊 :loud_sound:           Add or update logs
# 🔇 :mute:                 Remove logs
# 📁 :file_folder:          Perform database related changes
# 🌐 :globe_with_meridians: i18n and localization
# 👽 :alien:                Update code due to external API changes
# ----- fix -----
# ✏️ :pencil2:              Fix typos
# 🐛 :bug:                  Fix bugs
# 🚨 :rotating_light:       Fix compiler / Linter warnings
# 🚑 :ambulance:            Critical HOTFIX
# ----- WIP -----
# 🚧 :construction:         WIP(Work In Progress)
# 🍺 :beer:                 Write code drunkenly
# 💩 :poop:                 Write bad codes that needs to be improved
# ----- files or resources -----
# 🔧 :wrench:               Add or update configuration files
# 🔨 :hammer:               Add or update development scripts
# 💄 :lipstick:             Add or update the UI and style files
# 🍱 :bento:                Add or update assets
# 📝 :memo:                 Add or update documents
# 📄 :page_facing_up:       Add or update license
# 🔥 :fire:                 Remove code or files
# 🚚 :truck:                Move or rename resources (eg. files, paths, routes)
# ----- test -----
# ✅ :white_check_mark:     Add or update tests
# ✔️ :heavy_check_mark:     Make a test pass
# 🔒 :lock:                 Security-related improvements
# ----- dependnecies -----
# ➕ :heavy_plus_sign:      Add dependencies
# ➖ :heavy_minus_sign:     Remove dependencies
# ⬆️ :arrow_up:             Upgrade dependencies
# ⬇️ :arrow_down:           Downgrade dependencies
# 📌 :pushpin:              Pin dependencies to specific version
# ----- git operation -----
# 🔖 :bookmark:             Release / Version tags
# 👌 :ok_hand:              Review-related changes
# ⏪ :rewind:               Revert changes
# 🔀 :twisted_rightwards_arrows: Merge branches
# ----- CI -----
# 👷 :construction_worker:  Add or update CI build system
# 💚 :green_heart:          Fix CI build
# ----- shipping -----
# 🚀 :rocket:               Deploy stuff
# 📦 :package:              Add or update compiled files or packages
# ---- improvement -----
# 🎨 :art:                  Improve structure / format of the code.
# ⚡️ :zap:                  Improve performance
# ♿ :wheelchair:           Improve accessibility
# 🚸 :children_crossing:    Improve UX / usability
# 🔍 :mag:                  Improve SEO

# ==== The Seven Rules ====
# 1. Separate subject from body with a blank line
# 2. Limit the subject line to 50 characters
# 3. Capitalize the subject line
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period
# 5. Use the imperative mood in the subject line
# 6. Wrap the body at 72 characters
# 7. Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# How to Write a Git Commit Message http://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/

# for http://memo.goodpatch.co/2016/07/beautiful-commits-with-emojis/
